The price of insulated electrician safety helmets increases with the voltage protection level, with class C helmets being the most expensive, followed by class G and class E helmets.

12. What are the key features to look for when purchasing insulated electrician safety helmets?
Key features to consider when purchasing insulated electrician safety helmets include comfort, weight, impact resistance, insulation material, and adjustable chin straps.

13. What are the regulations and standards governing insulated electrician safety helmets?
Insulated electrician safety helmets must comply with standards such as ANSI/ISEA Z89.1 and ASTM F1449 to ensure their effectiveness and safety certification.

